dismissalText.commentary: Sanath Jayasuriya run out (Chigumbura) 9 (15b 0x4 0x6 39m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: absolutely brilliant fielding from Chigumbura after Jayasuriya went walk about at the non-striker's end. That wicket came from nowhere, but Jayasuriya was backing up too far and the Zimbabweans get their reward for some enthusiastic fielding. Jayasuriya walks off shaking his head

outstanding bowling from Malinga, the pace was too much for Chibhabha as he is caught on the crease and sends a thick edge towards third slip where Dilshan holds a sharp chance down by his ankles. Zimbabwe's top order again being blown away.

dismissalText.commentary: Tawanda Mupariwa b Malinga 20 (67b 2x4 0x6 68m) SR: 29.85

commentTextItems.html: finally Malinga gets one straight and Mupariwa misses a wild heave to bring this match to an end. The result has been known for much of Zimbabwe's innings but the Sri Lankan bowlers will be pleased with their run out, although there were a few too many extras once again

commentPostTextItems.html: So Sri Lanka make it two out of two in the Champions Trophy and are virtually assured of moving into the main section of the tournament. It still has to be settled but Sri Lanka have found some useful practice in these early matches.
The hightlight of the match was the batting of Upul Tharanga and Kumar Sangakkara. Tharanga made his second century in two matches before the Sri Lankan seamers ran through the Zimbabwean top order.

The next match is tomorrow between West Indies and Bangladesh and you can catch live coverage here on Cricinfo. We hope you have enjoyed today's match and from me, Andrew McGlashan, and Jenny Thompson it's goodbye for now and thanks for following the match with us.

dismissalComment.html: tries to clear long off but doesn't get hold of the lofted drive and is comfortably held by Matsikenyeri. An impressive innings from Sangakkara but now Sri Lanka have two new batsmen in the middle so maybe there's a chance for the Zimbabweans to keep the total down

image.caption: Tafadzwa Kamungozi
image.longCaption: Tafadzwa Kamungozi portrait, Chittagong, World T20, March 10, 2014

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Kamungozi b Utseya 6 (6b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: a bit of a soft dismissal. The batsman tried to paddle that, got a bit of a top edge and that's straight down's Kamungozi's throat at square leg, and the fielder makes no mistake. That's another blip in Sri Lanka's progress

dismissalText.commentary: Farveez Maharoof lbw b Kamungozi 13 (18b 1x4 0x6 16m) SR: 72.22

dismissalComment.html: that was a huge shout and a deserved wicket; the ball was nicely flighted and that pitched in line, turned a touch and that's the first wicket of the day for Kamungozi, his third in all.

image.longCaption: Tafadzwa Kamungozi portrait, Chittagong, World T20, March 10, 2014

dismissalText.commentary: Muthiah Muralidaran c Matsikenyeri b Kamungozi 10 (6b 2x4 0x6 6m) SR: 166.66

dismissalComment.html: that's clubbed off the bottom of the bat straight down long-off's throat and Muralitharan's cameo (10 from six balls) comes to an end

dismissalText.commentary: Tafadzwa Mufambisi c Jayawardene b Malinga 5 (9b 1x4 0x6 10m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: and another one goes. Huge waft away from his body against a delivery that bounces and Mufambisi sends a high edge flying towards Jayawardene at second slip, who this time makes no mistake and pouches it with two hands above his head. Sadly, it's a familiar tale for Zimbabwe but this is impressive bowling from Malinga

headshotImage.longCaption: Ruchira Perera player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Piet Rinke b Perera 1 (3b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: that was very much on the cards. Perera pitches up and finds a hint of inswing, a loose drive from Rinke takes the inside edge and crashes into the stumps.

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c Dilshan b Malinga 4 (12b 0x4 0x6 25m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: outstanding bowling from Malinga, the pace was too much for Chibhabha as he is caught on the crease and sends a thick edge towards third slip where Dilshan holds a sharp chance down by his ankles. Zimbabwe's top order again being blown away.

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c †Sangakkara b Maharoof 30 (56b 5x4 0x6 86m) SR: 53.57

dismissalComment.html: squared up by that one which was just leaving him and he got an edge on it which was cleanly taken with two hands by Sangakkara, away to his right. And that's a slow walk off for the batsman

headshotImage.caption: Dilhara Fernando player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dilhara Fernando player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor b Fernando 30 (40b 4x4 0x6 59m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: cleaned up with a pearler that came back in and went right through the gate, taking middle and off stumps. Another good fight from Taylor, with a very promising innings, comes to an end

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri c Jayasuriya b Fernando 2 (11b 0x4 0x6 26m) SR: 18.18

dismissalComment.html: you could see that wicket coming a mile off and it's Matsikenyeri who falls to the short ball as he can't get out of the way, the ball takes the glove and flies behind the wicket. Sangakkara tries to jump for it but Jayasuriya runs round and grabs a comfortable chance as the end gets closer for Zimbabwe

dismissalComment.html: launched into that one with positive intent but that's another wicket, with a run-out. Kamikaze call for a second run there and the batsman had no chance of getting back in as the bowler picked up the relay and threw it to Sangakkara who took the stumps cleanly

dismissalText.commentary: Prosper Utseya c Jayawardene b Muralidaran 20 (45b 3x4 0x6 60m) SR: 44.44

dismissalComment.html: edged and gone! Muralitharan gets a wicket with a doosra, with a simple feather straight to the welcoming hands of first slip. "Give Murali a stationary target long enough..." deadpans Jeff Dujon, and he couldn't be more right.

dismissalText.commentary: Tawanda Mupariwa b Malinga 20 (67b 2x4 0x6 68m) SR: 29.85

dismissalComment.html: finally Malinga gets one straight and Mupariwa misses a wild heave to bring this match to an end. The result has been known for much of Zimbabwe's innings but the Sri Lankan bowlers will be pleased with their run out, although there were a few too many extras once again

dismissalComment.html: another doosra and that's comprehensively beaten the batsman who was looking for the off-break, but it went the other way, just rubbing the outside edge and Sangakkara does the rest

stories.title: ICC Champions Trophy, 2006-07
stories.subTitle: 3rd Qualifying Match, Sri Lanka v Zimbabwe

stories.title: Sri Lanka v Zimbabwe, 3rd qualifying match, Ahmedabad
stories.subTitle: October 10, 2006
stories.summary: Match home for the Champions Trophy's third qualifying match between Sri Lanka and Zimbabwe at Ahmedabad

stories.title: Gently trampled upon
stories.subTitle: Sri Lanka v Zimbabwe, Ahmedabad
stories.summary: Zimbabwe put on a better show in their second game of the tournament - albeit by 56 runs - showing glimpses of genuine potential even as Sri Lanka muscled their way to two wins in as many games, and virtually assured themselves a place in the main draw
stories.byline: Verdict by Anand Vasu in Ahmedabad

stories.title: Tharanga stars in another win
stories.subTitle: Sri Lanka v Zimbabwe, 3rd qualifying match, Ahmedabad
stories.summary: Upul Tharanga's rich vein of form continued as he hammered his second hundred in a row and his fourth in nine innings to help Sri Lanka coast to a 144-run win against Zimbabwe and all but ensure a place in the main draw of the Champions Trophy.

stories.title: Sri Lanka aim for emphatic win
stories.subTitle: Sri Lanka v Zimbabwe, 3rd qualifying match, Ahmedabad
stories.seoTitle: Sri Lanka aim for emphatic win
stories.summary: The margin of defeat in the first game of the Champions Trophy - 37 runs - as Bangladesh succumbed to Sri Lanka was not an accurate reflection of the match as a competition
stories.byline: Preview by Anand Vasu in Ahmedabad

recentReportStory.title: Tharanga stars in another win
recentReportStory.subTitle: Sri Lanka v Zimbabwe, 3rd qualifying match, Ahmedabad
recentReportStory.summary: Upul Tharanga's rich vein of form continued as he hammered his second hundred in a row and his fourth in nine innings to help Sri Lanka coast to a 144-run win against Zimbabwe and all but ensure a place in the main draw of the Champions Trophy.
recentReportStory.credit: S Rajesh is stats editor of Cricinfo

recentPreviewStory.title: Sri Lanka aim for emphatic win
recentPreviewStory.subTitle: Sri Lanka v Zimbabwe, 3rd qualifying match, Ahmedabad
recentPreviewStory.seoTitle: Sri Lanka aim for emphatic win
recentPreviewStory.summary: The margin of defeat in the first game of the Champions Trophy - 37 runs - as Bangladesh succumbed to Sri Lanka was not an accurate reflection of the match as a competition
recentPreviewStory.byline: Preview by Anand Vasu in Ahmedabad
recentPreviewStory.credit: Anand Vasu is assistant editor of Cricinfo
